# Issues installing Expo

## Windows 
Do you have the following error when starting an Expo project on windows?

<img src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/10753152/65690550-25da0380-e024-11e9-8699-8cffb869787e.png">

This is because there is an incompatibility between the latest versions of Node.js and Expo. The solution is to install an older version of Node
- Uninstall Node
- Download a new version of Node:
- [X86](https://nodejs.org/dist/v10.16.3/node-v10.16.3-win-x86.zip)
- [64 bits](https://nodejs.org/dist/v10.16.3/node-v10.16.3-win-x64.zip)


## macOS

If you encounter permission errors while installing Expo:
`npm install expo-cli --global`

Use sudo:

`sudo npm install expo-cli --global`
